                <h3>Dyslipidemia in Primary Care: Addressing Barriers to Optimal Lipid Management</h3><h3>
                    ABOUT:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li> Dyslipidemia in Primary Care: Addressing Barriers to Optimal Lipid Management is an interactive and evidence-based program developed by leading Canadian experts to address the importance of strict management of low density lipoprotein cholesterol (LDL-C) for patients with atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease as well as provide a timely review of the results of recently completed clinical trials and their applicability to routine clinical practice.</li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>
                    FORMAT:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li> The Dyslipidemia in Primary Care: Addressing Barriers to Optimal Lipid Management program consists of an interactive core didactic deck and two short discussion-oriented modules.&nbsp; </li>
                    <li>The program can be presented with just the core deck (60 minutes – 1.0 Mainpro+) or with the addition of the two modules (90 minutes – 1.5 Mainpro+) </li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>CERTIFICATION:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li> This Group Learning activity has been certified for up to 1.5 MAINPRO+ one-credit-per-hour credits by the CFPC. &nbsp;</li>
                    <li>You may offer the program to your customers as a 60-minute (1.0 Mainpro+ Credit) program or a 90-minute (1.5 Mainpro+ credits) program. Please reference the Process Manual for a detailed description of the program and the applicable credit hours.</li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>
                    SPEAKERS:
                </h3>
                <ul>
                    <li> Program speakers will have access to the program materials once they confirm availability for at least one of regional event dates.</li>
                    <li>A copy of their COI slides is available in their resource for download.</li>
                    <li>A speaker training video facilitated by Dr. Lawrence Leiter will be made available in the speaker portal.  Dr. Leiter provides a topline summary of the accredited CPD deck and highlights the key teaching points.</li>
                    <li>Please reference the Process Manual for important information and requirements</li>
                    <li><strong>As per the CFPC guidelines for certified programs, speakers are required to use the presentation slides provided by the physician organization and are not permitted to make any changes to the program materials/slides.</strong></li>
                </ul>
                <p></p><h3>
